cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.LG 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as named entity recognition and stance detection. Additionally, it may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the study focuses on social media texts. It could also be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the study involves extracting information from text data. Furthermore, it could be classified under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) as stance detection is a sub-topic of sentiment analysis, which is related to emotions and feelings expressed in text. Lastly, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as machine learning techniques are used in both named entity recognition and stance detection tasks.
